# üêõ Dropdown Readability Fix - Light Mode

## ‚úÖ **RESOLVED** - July 1, 2025

Fixed dropdown menu readability issue in light mode where select options were unreadable due to dark styling being applied.

## üö® **Problem Description**

**Issue**: When switching from dark mode to light mode, dropdown menus (select elements) became unreadable
- Dark background with dark text
- Affected all dropdown menus across the application
- Made project selection, workspace selection, and other dropdowns unusable

**Root Cause**: CSS was only defining dark mode styles for select elements, without explicit light mode styles

## üîß **Solution Applied**

### **CSS Changes Made**

**Before** (Problematic CSS):
```css
/* Only dark mode styles defined */
html.dark select.form-input {
    background-color: #1f2937;
    color: #ffffff;
}

html.dark select.form-input option {
    background-color: #1f2937 !important;
    color: #ffffff !important;
}
```

**After** (Fixed CSS):
```css
/* Light mode select styling - ensure readability */
select.form-input {
    background-color: #ffffff;
    color: #1f2937;
}

select.form-input option {
    background-color: #ffffff !important;
    color: #1f2937 !important;
}

/* Dark mode select styling */
html.dark select.form-input {
    background-color: #1f2937;
    color: #ffffff;
}

html.dark select.form-input option {
    background-color: #1f2937 !important;
    color: #ffffff !important;
}
```

### **Key Improvements**

1. **‚úÖ Explicit Light Mode Styling**
   - White background (#ffffff) with dark text (#1f2937)
   - Applied to both `select` elements and `option` elements
   - Uses `!important` to override browser defaults

2. **‚úÖ Maintained Dark Mode Functionality**
   - Dark background (#1f2937) with white text (#ffffff)
   - Existing dark mode behavior preserved
   - Proper contrast maintained in both modes

3. **‚úÖ Cross-Browser Compatibility**
   - Force styling with `!important` overrides browser defaults
   - Consistent appearance across different browsers
   - Works with system preference detection

## üì± **Affected Components**

**Dropdown Menus Fixed**:
- Project selector in top navigation
- Workspace selector in bottom status bar
- Task status dropdowns in forms
- Priority level selectors
- User assignment dropdowns
- Webhook event selection menus

